### What problem does this feature solve?
When using API to obtain data asynchronously, if deep data is used in the template, an error is often reported and execution cannot continue. It is hoped that an error handling proxy can be added, and undefined will be returned when an error occurs.

### What does the proposed API look like?
```javascript
function getDeepObjectValue(obj, path) {
    if (Array.isArray(path)) {
        path = path.join(".");
    }
    if (!obj) return undefined;
    try {
        if (!path) return obj;
        return path.split(".").reduce((o, i) => o[i], obj);
    } catch (error) {
        return undefined;
    }
}
```

